</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Impact on child survival </strong>- Research indicates that timely and effective first aid can significantly reduce fatalities and severe outcomes in emergency situations.










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-39_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-40_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - This mandates that employers, including those in education and childcare settings, ensure adequate first aid provision.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) 2021</strong> - Specifically requires paediatric first aid training for at least one person in early years settings who is available at all times.










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-48_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-49_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-50_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices in paediatric first aid</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-52_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Immediate response</strong> - Quick response times are critical in paediatric emergencies due to the smaller physiological reserve in children.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training</strong> - Continuous updating of skills through accredited courses, such as those offered by The Mandatory Training Group, ensures readiness and competence.











